subtitle: Our new attitude that we apply
as we enter this New Year
can actually draw down and draw inward
into your life into the life of your loved ones
something new
which gives you the power, the courage, the hope, the confidence
to be able to take on any challenge
with new strengths, new possibilities
even if yesterday you felt you couldn't do it.
No matter what you've gone through, no matter how much you feel you may be injured,
here is a new opportunity.
A new energy enters into your very being
to the very fiber of your existence
giving you a new opportunity.
Don't allow the past to haunt your future.
Don't allow circumstances to define you.
Don't allow pain and loss to determine your identity.
You don't know what kind of reservoirs of strengths you have.
You have a Divine Force within you
and that is an infinite reservoir of power.
So we are brimming with all kinds of power and energy.
Rosh Hashana comes and an energy from outside enters
into the stratosphere into our existence
completely unprecedented
helping us do unprecedented things.
A New Year: A New You
